        "**Common traps:**\n"
        "- Confusing **complementary** (sum = 90) with **supplementary** (sum = 180). A trick: C comes before S in the alphabet, and 90 comes before 180.\n"
        "- Forgetting the exterior angle theorem and instead computing the interior angle first, wasting time.\n"
        "- In similar triangles, squaring the side ratio for area but forgetting to square it (using the ratio directly for area).\n\n"
        "**Tip:** When a diagram shows parallel lines, immediately label every angle you know and mark equal pairs with matching tick marks. One labeled angle typically unlocks all eight angles in the figure, turning a complex-looking problem into straightforward substitution."
