        "**Applications:**\n"
        "- **Diagonal of a rectangle:** A rectangle with sides l and w has diagonal d = sqrt(l^2 + w^2).\n"
        "- **Height of an equilateral triangle:** For an equilateral triangle with side s, the height is (s*sqrt(3))/2 (drop an altitude to split it into two 30-60-90 triangles).\n"
        "- **3D diagonal of a box:** For a box with dimensions l, w, h, the space diagonal is sqrt(l^2 + w^2 + h^2). Apply the Pythagorean theorem twice (or recognize it as one extended formula).\n\n"
